=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_GlitchRHPF_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright clean sound, with complex oscillator character around 50 Hz, featuring slow attack and compressed envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, and filtered with steep_rolloff character.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: slow
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: compressed
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: clean
  spectral_complexity_mean: moderate
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 50.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -1.4017
  harmonic_regularity: 0.7518
  pitch_clarity: 101.7167
  inharmonicity: 0.0270
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -6.8160
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: GlitchRHPF Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/GlitchRHPF.html
// Tags: GlitchRHPF, Classes, filter
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
//code that utilizes the glitch.
//warning!  extremely loud.
//note: might not sound the same on all soundcards
(
{GlitchRHPF.ar(
    BrownNoise.ar(1.dup),
    0.5,
    Saw.kr(1, 10)
)}.play;
)
